<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: Classic Shell Toolbar missing on Windows 8 Pro]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=3180&amp;p=14936#p14936"><![CDATA[
<div class="quotetitle">GauravK wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br />Try these steps: <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.classicshell.net/faq/#explorer_toolbar">http://www.classicshell.net/faq/#explorer_toolbar</a><!-- m --> According to your screenshots, the addons are already enabled as instructed in step 1, but the setting in step 2 might be off. After that, for Windows 8, you must open the <strong>View</strong> tab of the Ribbon (in Spanish it seems to be called <strong>Vista <img src="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/images/smilies/icon_mrgreen.gif" alt=":mrgreen:" title="Mr. Green" /> </strong>). Click on the down arrow in the &quot;Options&quot; section. Select &quot;Classic Explorer Bar&quot;. Any Explorer toolbars or addons can be enabled from there.<br /></div><br /><br /><br />Thank you very much!!!  <img src="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/images/smilies/icon_e_biggrin.gif" alt=":D" title="Very Happy" /><br /><br /><img src="http://i61.tinypic.com/xpa8f6.jpg" alt="" /><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=4491">@ndres</a> — Fri Sep 19, 2014 3:43 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
