<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: Classic Shell Toolbar missing on Windows 8 Pro]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=3180&amp;p=14907#p14907"><![CDATA[
Try these steps: <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.classicshell.net/faq/#explorer_toolbar">http://www.classicshell.net/faq/#explorer_toolbar</a><!-- m --> According to your screenshots, the addons are already enabled as instructed in step 1, but the setting in step 2 might be off. After that, for Windows 8, you must open the <strong>View</strong> tab of the Ribbon (in Spanish it seems to be called <strong>Vista <img src="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/images/smilies/icon_mrgreen.gif" alt=":mrgreen:" title="Mr. Green" /> </strong>). Click on the down arrow in the &quot;Options&quot; section. Select &quot;Classic Explorer Bar&quot;. Any Explorer toolbars or addons can be enabled from there.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=54">Gaurav</a> — Thu Sep 18, 2014 4:47 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
</entry>
